BugPattern.ShortDescription: Method uses the same code for two branches
BugPattern.Details: This method uses the same code to implement two branches of a conditional branch. Check to ensure that this isn't a coding mistake.
A mutable static field could be changed by malicious code or by accident. The field could be made package protected to avoid this vulnerability.

This instruction assigns a value to a local variable, but the value is not read or used in any subsequent instruction. Often, this indicates an error, because the value computed is never used.

Note that Sun's javac compiler often generates dead stores for final local variables. Because FindBugs is a bytecode-based tool, there is no easy way to eliminate these false positives.

BugPattern.ShortDescription: Class defines clone() but doesn't implement Cloneable
BugPattern.Details: This class defines a clone() method but the class doesn't implement Cloneable. There are some situations in which this is OK (e.g., you want to control how subclasses can clone themselves), but just make sure that this is what you intended.
